olive oil
1 cucumber
1 carrot
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet pork mince
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 tsp honey
drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• Thinly slice cucumber. Using a vegetable peeler, slice carrot into ribbons. Finely chop baby leaves.

• In a medium bowl, combine pork mince, Aussie spice blend, grated Parmesan cheese, baby leaves, fine breadcrumbs and the egg.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of pork mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per person). Transfer to a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and cooked through, 8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Set aside.
• In a large bowl, combine the honey and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Add mixed salad leaves, cucumber and carrot. Toss to combine and season to taste.

• Divide cucumber salad between bowls. Top with Parmesan pork meatballs.
• Drizzle over dill & parsley mayonnaise to serve. Enjoy!